EXPECTED RESULTS
================================================================================

After execution (with pipelining working correctly):

REGISTERS:
$v0 = 0x0040 (64)
$v1 = 0x0010 (16)
$v2 = 0x0005 (5)
$v3 = 0x000A (10)
$t0 = 0x003F (63) - result of ABS(-1)
$a0 = 0x001A (after 5 loop iterations)
$a1 = 0x0000 (loop counter exhausted)

MEMORY:
Mem[0x20] = 0x003F  # ABS result
Mem[0x22] = 0x0005  # MIN(5, 10) = 5
Mem[0x24] = 0x000A  # MAX(5, 10) = 10
Mem[0x10] = 0x0141  # Original 0x0101 + 0x40
Mem[0x12] = 0x0150  # Original 0x0110 + 0x40
... etc

================================================================================
NOP RULES SUMMARY
================================================================================

1. After R-type/I-type that writes register:
   ? Insert 2 NOPs before using that register

2. After load (lw):
   ? Insert 1 NOP before using loaded data

3. After branch/jump:
   ? Insert 2 NOPs in delay slots

4. After store (sw):
   ? No NOPs needed (doesn't write register)

5. After immediate instructions (ori, addi, etc):
   ? Insert 2 NOPs before using result

